              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Pd/TiHx/Si was prepared by magnetron sputtering",
                "method, which was 1.8E17 atoms/cm2 H atoms in a 1.2E17",
                "atoms/cm2 Ti film. A Pd overlayer of 2.4E16 atoms/cm2",
                "was deposited onto the Ti film.",
                "The areal density of H relative to Pd was determined",
                "by their scattering with 12C assuming Rutherford",
                "scattering."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An Au/Si surface barrier detector was placed",
                "at a backscattering angle, subtended a solid angle of",
                "1.12E-3 sr defined by a 3x4 mm slit. Two detectors,",
                "one to detect the H recoils at a recoil angle of 30",
                "degree and the other to measure the backscattered",
                "yield of the incident 12C particles at a scattering",
                "angle of 165 degree."
              ]
            }
          ],
